('snapsheet', 'Snapsheet', 'Cloud claims management platform with AI-powered appraisal and virtual adjustment workflows',
 E'Snapsheet is a cloud-native claims management platform that digitises and automates the auto insurance claims workflow from first notice of loss through settlement. The platform combines a consumer-facing mobile app for photo-based damage submission, an AI-powered appraisal engine that generates repair estimates from submitted photos, and a cloud claims management system that handles adjusters, body shops, rental coordination, and payment processing in a unified workflow.\n\nThe virtual adjustment model is the core value proposition: policyholders submit photos of vehicle damage through the Snapsheet app, the AI appraisal engine analyses the images and generates a repair estimate, and adjusters review and approve the estimate through the cloud management interface - eliminating the need for a field adjuster to physically visit the vehicle. For auto insurers processing high volumes of collision and comprehensive claims, this workflow reduces cost per claim by 20-40% while improving customer experience through faster settlement timelines.\n\nSnapsheet''s technology serves both carriers running their own claims operations and third-party administrators handling claims on behalf of carriers. The platform processes millions of claims annually and has established integrations with major body shop networks, rental car providers, and payment systems. The AI appraisal engine is continuously trained on new claims data to improve estimate accuracy across vehicle types and damage scenarios. Snapsheet also offers a white-label version of the consumer app allowing carriers to deploy virtual adjustment capabilities under their own brand. Enterprise pricing is structured on claim volume basis and requires direct sales engagement.',
 'https://snapsheet.me', 'https://snapsheet.me',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.3, 890, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['insurance', 'claims-management', 'ai-assistants'],
 ARRAY['Virtual adjustment workflow reduces cost per auto claim by 20-40% vs field adjuster model', 'Consumer mobile app provides convenient photo submission and claim status tracking', 'Integrated with body shop networks and rental providers for end-to-end claim coordination', 'White-label option lets carriers deploy under own brand without custom technology development'],
 ARRAY['Auto-focused - property and other casualty lines have limited native support', 'Consumer app adoption requires policyholder willingness to self-serve damage documentation', 'Enterprise pricing and implementation scale - not suitable for small insurers or MGAs', 'AI estimate accuracy on severe or complex damage scenarios may require adjuster review'],
