('socotra', 'Socotra', 'Modern cloud-native policy administration system for insurers launching and managing products faster',
 E'Socotra is a cloud-native policy administration system built for insurers that want to launch new products, enter new markets, and update existing coverages faster than legacy policy administration systems allow. Traditional policy administration systems - often built in the 1980s and 1990s - require 12-24 month implementation timelines and expensive IT projects to change product terms, rates, or forms. Socotra''s modern architecture allows product teams to configure and launch new insurance products in weeks using a JSON-based product definition system that does not require traditional policy system development cycles.\n\nThe platform handles the full policy lifecycle: quoting, binding, endorsements, renewals, and cancellations across personal and commercial lines. The rating engine supports complex actuarial tables and rules without requiring IT involvement for routine rate changes, putting product and underwriting teams in control of pricing updates on timelines that match market dynamics rather than IT sprint schedules. The API-first architecture means Socotra integrates easily with digital distribution channels, third-party data providers, and ecosystem tools rather than requiring a closed proprietary ecosystem.\n\nSocotra''s AI capabilities are embedded in the product configuration and underwriting rules layers - enabling underwriting teams to build and deploy machine learning models for risk scoring directly within the policy administration workflow. The platform is used by innovators across the insurance spectrum: incumbent carriers modernising legacy systems, MGAs launching specialty programmes, and insurtechs building digital-first insurance products. Pricing is enterprise SaaS structured on policy volume and product complexity. Socotra supports deployments in the US, UK, and international markets.',
 'https://socotra.com', 'https://socotra.com',
 'paid', false, 0, 4.4, 870, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['insurance', 'policy-administration', 'analytics'],
 ARRAY['Product teams can launch new insurance products in weeks vs 12-24 months on legacy systems', 'JSON-based product configuration eliminates IT dependency for routine product and rate changes', 'API-first architecture integrates with distribution channels and data providers without custom development', 'Supports personal and commercial lines across US and international markets'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise-only pricing requires significant implementation investment for initial deployment', 'Full migration from legacy policy administration systems is a multi-year project for large carriers', 'Requires product and underwriting team configuration expertise to realise speed advantage', 'Smaller ecosystem of certified integration partners than established legacy PAS vendors'],
