('coalition', 'Coalition', 'Active cyber insurance that combines AI-powered risk monitoring with cyber coverage for businesses',
 E'Coalition is a cyber insurance provider that pairs insurance coverage with active risk monitoring technology, positioning its product as cyber risk management rather than pure insurance. Every Coalition policyholder receives access to Coalition Control - a continuous security monitoring platform that scans the company''s external attack surface, monitors for credential exposures on the dark web, identifies unpatched software vulnerabilities, and flags domain spoofing or phishing infrastructure targeting the business. When the monitoring identifies a high-severity risk, Coalition''s security team contacts the policyholder directly with remediation guidance before a claim occurs.\n\nThe AI underwriting model uses the same external security scanning data for risk pricing that the monitoring platform uses for ongoing risk management. This creates a more accurate underwriting picture than traditional cyber insurance applications, which rely on self-reported security controls that may be inaccurate or outdated. The result is pricing that more closely reflects actual external attack surface exposure rather than survey response data.\n\nFor small and mid-market businesses that need cyber insurance, Coalition''s bundled model - coverage plus monitoring - delivers a combined value proposition that separates it from pure insurance carriers and pure security monitoring vendors. The claims team includes a cyber incident response capability that deploys when a covered incident occurs, providing forensic investigation, breach notification support, and regulatory compliance guidance alongside the financial coverage. Coalition writes coverage for businesses across the US and Canada, with limits up to $15 million for eligible SMBs. Pricing starts around $100/month for small business coverage and scales with revenue, industry, and security posture.',
 'https://coalitioninc.com', 'https://coalitioninc.com',
 'paid', false, 100, 4.5, 2100, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['insurance', 'cybersecurity', 'fintech'],
 ARRAY['Active risk monitoring included at no additional cost alongside cyber insurance coverage', 'AI underwriting uses real security scan data rather than self-reported application responses', 'Coalition Control identifies credential exposures and vulnerabilities before they become claims', 'In-house incident response team deploys immediately when a covered cyber incident occurs'],
 ARRAY['Coverage limited to cyber risks - not a full commercial insurance provider', 'Security monitoring scope is external attack surface only - does not include internal network monitoring', 'Higher-revenue or higher-risk businesses may face pricing that exceeds traditional cyber insurer rates', 'US and Canada only - not available for businesses operating primarily outside North America'],
 ARRAY['SMBs and mid-market companies wanting cyber insurance that actively reduces their risk exposure', 'Technology companies and professional services firms with elevated cyber risk profiles', 'Businesses that have experienced a prior cyber incident and need both coverage and ongoing monitoring'],
 NOW()),

('next-insurance', 'Next Insurance', 'AI-powered small business insurance platform for instant digital coverage across 1,300 professions',
 E'Next Insurance is an AI-powered small business insurance platform that offers instant digital coverage for over 1,300 business types, delivering general liability, professional liability, commercial auto, workers compensation, and tools and equipment coverage through a fully digital application and policy management experience. The platform was designed to replace the traditional small business insurance process - calling a broker, waiting for quotes, and faxing signed documents - with an online experience that generates a tailored policy in under 10 minutes.\n\nThe underwriting AI analyses the applicant''s business type, revenue, number of employees, and business activities to generate accurate coverage recommendations and instant pricing without a broker intermediary. The model was trained on small business insurance loss data across hundreds of professions to price risk at a level of granularity that traditional broker-based channels cannot deliver cost-effectively. Policyholders manage their coverage, issue certificates of insurance, and file claims entirely through the Next Insurance app or web portal.\n\nFor small business owners who buy insurance because they must - to satisfy a client contract requirement, a lease agreement, or a state licensing requirement - Next Insurance delivers the fastest path from need to coverage. The instant certificate of insurance feature is particularly valued by contractors and service businesses that need to issue certificates on demand for clients and project owners. The claims experience uses a digital-first process with AI-assisted initial triage, with human adjusters engaged for complex or disputed claims. Next Insurance is available in all 50 US states and covers over 480,000 small businesses. Pricing starts from $25/month for basic general liability coverage for solo operators.',
